caption: Tasty and healthy food with ample combination possibilities. I had the Hawaiian bowl and was awesome.

I love poke bowl Greensboro! The location in downtown Greensboro and its delicious taste make it an incredible option. You can personalize your bowl or burrito with anything you want in it for an affordable price. The taste is amazing.
So delicious and filling. This is one of the few places that my wife and I get strong cravings for.

Love this place. A unique combination of healthy, tasty, and fulfilling freshly made poke. Price is certainly moderate if compared to any sushi. Highly recommended!
The staff was very kind and the food tasted fresh.
I don't know what half the stuff I ate was, but me and my friend absolutely loved. 10/10 Will easily recommend.

Healthy and tasty. Fresh veggies, good rice and lots of protein options.

Me and my partner visited here this past weekend, and we’re glad we did! We got a poke bowel with tuna and salmon. They have many toppings and sauces, and allow you to try the sauces to see what you would like. We will definitely get takeout here again for a date night in!

Great food! Great service! Will definitely be back! Only wish is for beer! 5 stars!

Average poke bowl but the ingredients were fresh and quite tasty. I highly recommend the House Special which includes ahi tuna, salmon, yellow tail and shrimp. Not a bad go-to spot for healthy(ish) lunch.
This was my first time, but the staff was very friendly and helpful, the food was very enjoyable. Definitely will be going back again.
Amazing Poke Bowl place! The ingredients are super fresh and the portions are BIG! This is the type of food that you feel great after eating! Super healthy and nutritious. Give it a try

Omg! When I say don’t think just go! So fresh and yummy! The staff is so friendly and amazing. I’m addicted to the spicy dragon bowl ... my 3rd time eating it and it didn’t disappoint at all. The 5 stars are well deserved.

Great fresh ingredients, awesome service and never busy in the mornings. I enjoy sitting with the Aloha bowl with a nice game.
First time ACTUALLY eating here. For what I got and the price I paid, EXCELLENT!!!!! I'll go back!!!!

Absolutely amazing.  Fresh ingredients and good service.  Lots of choices.  This place is perfect for our family of 5 because everyone can Customize their meals to a tee!  Plenty of options to choose from.  Walkable from all of downtown and next to Center City Park.
Unfortunately underwhelmed. They didn’t have ac in the summer and were serving raw fish which is more than a little concerning. I wanted the poke bowls to be good but I was pretty disappointed.

Oh so good!

Reasonable price and Fresh Salmon!

I am an absolute fan of the Spicy Dragon Bowl. So delicious!
Friendly staff, delicious and fresh food.
The signature bowls are great.  There are also plenty of options for make your own!
Lunch time favorite spot for a quick fresh meal downtown. Nothing fancy, straightforward and delicious. I tried the original poki bowl and for the price it was surprisingly filling.

If you enjoy sushi then you’ll absolutely love this place.  Poke is almost like a sushi salad of pure deliciousness. Super fresh and tasty ingredients. Plenty of meat and vegetable options to choose from. Can’t recommend this place enough.
Very different Asian concept from what I am used to. Delicious food, great expereince!

This is a great spot in downtown to eat at.  The food was fresh and the display was very clean.  A welcome change from some of the other bowl eateries around town.  The staff was very friendly and the prices are reasonable.  This is a must try!
Best poke bowl I have had in NC!  Fresh ingredients, generous portions, fair price.  Will be back for sure.
My boyfriend and I absolutely love this place and visit once a week! Fresh, healthy and delicious food! We also love the friendly service
Great friendly service with fantastic fresh food! I ordered the Hawaiian Classic, added extra mango and avocado, and it is delish! Will be coming back often!

The food is absolutely fresh and DELICIOUS. The staff is very friendly.  The House Classic Bowl is FANTASTIC. You can also make your own.  Great location in Downtown Greensboro on N. Elm St.  The decoration is very simple, it can definitely be improved. Open until 8 pm, for summer they should open until 9 or 10 pm.
I love this place! The rice is so fluffy, everything is so fresh and clean. I adore how well they take care of everything.
